The paper deals with motion planning, which is a subfield of robotics (cs.RO). It also involves developing an anytime planning algorithm using a belief model, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The algorithm is designed to search for paths that are Pareto-optimal in path length and collision probability, which involves optimization and machine learning techniques (cs.LG). The paper also mentions dealing with collision checking, which is a common problem in control systems and robotics (cs.SY). Finally, the paper evaluates the algorithm on high-dimensional motion-planning problems, which may involve computer vision techniques for perception and sensing (cs.CV).
